Many exception are here in python but in this topic we will see  some common exceptions

1)'TypeError' Exception
     ->this occurs when invalid operations between data types
     try:
           a=input()
           b=int(input())
           print(a/b)   
    except TypeError as e:          #output
          print("type error:",e)        #type error: unsupported operand type(s) for /: 'str' and 'int' 
                                    #Because 'a' is string and 'b' is int so,string cannot divide by int


2)'NameError' Exception
      -?this occurs when variable name is not define
      try:
            a=int(input())
            b=int(input())
            print(a/c)               #output
      except NameError as e:           #name error: name 'c' is not defined
           print("name error:",e)   #because c is not defined in this code


3)'ValueError' Exception
       ->this occurs when enter invalid data type conversion
       try:
           a=int(input())
           b=int(input())
           print(a+b)                    #output
       except ValueError as e:             # value error: invalid literal for int() with base 10: 'as' 
           print("value error:",e)     #because asked integer but enter string so occurs error


